      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this way, and I want to acknowledge the sheer weight of that loss. Losing years of work and feeling like a ghost is an incredibly painful and isolating experience. Please know that your identity is not defined solely by your research or your papers; you are a person with value beyond your data.\n\nWhile I cannot undo the past or bring back the lost files, I can offer a different perspective on how to move forward. Sometimes, when we lose everything we built, we need to step back and look at the bigger picture. It's a good time to take a break, perhaps even a long one, to let your mind rest.\n\nIf you are feeling overwhelmed, please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional who can provide support during this difficult time. You are not alone in this, and there are people who care about you.",
